cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to disambiguate and discover entities and relations in text streams. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes an end-to-end trainable memory network, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with unsupervised learning and one-shot learning, which are topics covered in cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques to build a knowledge base, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with neural networks and their training, which is a topic covered in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
